BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Thursday: machine & Tremor Cordis: An in-progress sharing of new d
 evised adaptations\, conceived and directed by Roger Ellis and Kathryn Wal
 sh
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T000000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T013000Z
UID:ed7c19e91004a4aae4802c682cc51e10@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Thursday: machine\nAdapted and Directed by Roger Ellis\nDevise
 d with Sharon Miles\, Alex O’Shea\, and Kevin Aoussou\nLighting Design b
 y Surya Saathi\n\nAn unfaithful adaptation of The Man Who Was Thursday and
  The Machine Stops\, this new work stages a collision between unlikely sou
 rces to ask: what happens when the surveilled return the gaze?\n\nThe audi
 ence is drawn into a conspiracy where not everyone is who they claim to be
 . As loyalties shift and identities blur\, the only certainty is that the 
 rules of the game are changing.\n\nWhat is your next move?\n\nTremor Cordi
 s\nAdapted by Liz Hayes and Kathryn Walsh\nMusic by Robert Frost\nDirected
  by Kathryn Walsh\nDevised with Alexander Gemignani and Shawn Pfautsch\nLi
 ghting Design by Isabella Castro\nShakespeare’s The Winter’s Tale gets
  ransacked and re-focused on the domestic and familial. With music\, ritua
 l\, three performers\, and Shakespeare’s text\, we use the big questions
  of an old play to look at our current world: What patterns of authority a
 nd control do we inherit and reproduce? What takes us from partners to adv
 ersaries? Can we move from grief to forgiveness?
LOCATION:Abbott Hall\, 710 N. Lake Shore Drive\, Chicago\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/640558
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
