BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Curator tour: Three Steps Forward\, Two Steps Back: The Continued 
 Struggle to Treat Mental Illness in America
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T180000Z
UID:7f0db55647dfef74820b56287b04d0ad@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Join curators for a tour of the new exhibit\, Three Steps Forw
 ard\, Two Steps Back: The Continued Struggle to Treat Mental Illness in Am
 erica\, currently on display in the Eckenhoff Reading Room at Galter Libra
 ry. \nThis exhibit explores both societal and medical treatments of menta
 l illness in the US from the 18th century to today. It highlights institut
 ional confinement\, medical and pharmaceutical treatments\, the developmen
 t of child psychiatry\, and the shift to police as mental illness first re
 sponders. Patterns of advancement and retreat carry through each case\, sh
 owing the struggle to properly treat mental illness continues today.  \nV
 iew Three Steps Forward\, Two Steps Back online.
LOCATION:Ward Building\, 303 E. Chicago Avenue\, Chicago\, IL
URL:https://galter.northwestern.edu/exhibits/28
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
