SUMMARY:Chicago Language Symposium 2026
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T140000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T220000Z
UID:67ba6c8a38c8d33a65db9d5819634c64@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:2026 Chicago Language Symposium\nSurviving in a Time of Change
 : Embracing Challenges as Opportunities\nSaturday\, April 18th 2026\n\nOnl
 ine via Zoom\; All times Central\n\nAt a time of anticipated and unanticip
 ated change\, what steps can we take to meet students where they are while
  strengthening and sustaining our programs?\nThe 2026 Chicago Language Sym
 posium will discuss this and other questions on April 18\, 2026. To make s
 ure the symposium is accessible to presenters and participants across the 
 country\, it will be held entirely online via Zoom.\nThe Symposium is pres
 ented by the University of Chicago Language Center\ntogether with:\nThe Co
 uncil of Language Instruction and the Language Resource Center at Northwes
 tern University\nThe Sandi Port Errant Language and Culture Learning Cente
 r at the University of Illinois-ChicagoThe Department of Modern Languages 
 at DePaul University\nLearn more about the Symposium below\, and contact C
 athy Baumann at ccbauman@uchicago.edu with questions. We sincerely hope yo
 u can join us.
URL:https://languages.uchicago.edu/cls2026/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
