DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T020000Z
UID:d14152367e9e514c33c788c2d6ccae63@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Harvey Felder\, conductor\; Desirée Ruhstrat\, violin\nThe or
 chestra presents Arnold Bax’s cheerful and bubbling Dance in the Sunligh
 t. Clarice Assad’s Violin Concerto features lecturer of violin Desirée 
 Ruhstrat. Concluding the evening is Beethoven’s Symphony No. 2 in D Majo
 r\, Op. 36\, a relentlessly cheerful work punctuated by moments of melanch
 oly.\nArnold Bax\, Dance in the Sunlight from Three Pieces for Small Orche
 stra\nClarice Assad\, Violin Concerto\nLudwig van Beethoven\, Symphony No.
  2 in D Major\, Op. 36
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-university-cham
 ber-orchestra-9
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
