BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Symphonic Wind Ensemble and Combined Choirs: Sacred and Profane
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260503T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260503T020000Z
UID:28a0b430f62fd8152bed9aecfef521b0@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Andrew Megill\, A. J. Keller\, and Robert Taylor\, conductors\
 nCombined Bienen School choirs and the Symphonic Wind Ensemble join forces
  for a unique collaboration exploring music of awe\, reverence\, and fate.
  The program opens with Randall Thompson’s stirring The Last Words of Da
 vid and Anton Bruckner’s monumental Mass No. 2 in E Minor. Brahms’s no
 ble Begräbnisgesang (Burial Song) offers a moment of reflective solemnity
 \, setting the stage for the raw energy of Carl Orff’s Carmina Burana in
  its thrilling arrangement for chorus and wind ensemble. This unforgettabl
 e night showcases the full expressive spectrum of voices and winds from th
 e sacred to the elemental.\nRandall Thompson\, The Last Words of David\nAn
 ton Bruckner\, Mass No. 2 in E Minor\, WAB 27\nJohannes Brahms\, Begräbni
 sgesang (Burial Song)\, Op. 13\nCarl Orff (trans. Juan Vicente Mas Quiles)
 \, Carmina Burana\, Part 1
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/symphonic-wind-ensemble-and-
 combined-choirs
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
