DESCRIPTION:Wildcats in Water Student Seminar Series — Each month\, stud
 ents share their innovative water research in engaging flash talks\, follo
 wed by valuable networking opportunities with snacks and drinks. These gat
 herings are designed to create meaningful connections within our water com
 munity while showcasing the exciting work students are doing across discip
 lines. Open to all students and faculty\, Wildcats in Water offers a perfe
 ct blend of peer learning and social interaction in a welcoming environmen
 t.\n🕦 11:30 AM – 12:30 PM\n📍 2205 Tech Drive\, First Floor\, Room 
 1-160\nThis is a great chance to learn about innovative research in wastew
 ater and connect with peers across disciplines. We encourage you to forwar
 d this to your peers and students. Lunch will be provided.\nPlease fill ou
 t this interest form or Email us at: water@northwestern.edu
