BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Concert Band: Celebration
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260516T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260516T020000Z
UID:f1718b3579b5a14fe4eef485ab5ae7cf@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Daniel J. Farris\, conductor\nDirector of Athletic Bands Danie
 l J. Farris conducts his final concert after 26 years at Northwestern\, wh
 ere he led the “Wildcat” Marching Band and Concert Band. Prior to his 
 time at Northwestern\, Farris served as Assistant Director of Bands at Ill
 inois State University and the University of Nevada\, Las Vegas. He was al
 so director of Orlando’s Walt Disney World Collegiate All-Star Band and 
 taught in Minnesota and Wisconsin public schools. Bands under his directio
 n have performed at the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade\, Bands of Americ
 a Regional and National Championships\, Ireland’s St. Patrick’s Day Pa
 rade in Dublin\, and numerous bowl games. In this farewell concert\, talen
 ted students from across the Northwestern campus present a range of exciti
 ng repertoire for band.
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/concert-band-4
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
