BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Artist Talk - Quan Zhou\, Artist in Residence
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260519T213000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260519T230000Z
UID:f32d31095f7fe103dc46127e140c701c@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:As the culminating event of her artist residency at Northweste
 rn\, Quan Zhou will present Linaje (Lineage)\, a transmedia installation t
 hat reconstructs the artist’s lost ancestry through AI-generated histori
 es and artifacts—photographs\, documents\, drawings\, and heirloom objec
 ts. In this public talk\, she will discuss fundamental questions faced by 
 first-generation descendants of migrants whose genealogies are erased\, fr
 agmented\, or illegible.\nThis event is still in the planning stages\; ple
 ase check back closer to May 19 for full details!\nQuan Zhou is the Spring
  2026 Artist in Residence of the Department of Spanish and Portuguese and 
 the Kaplan Humanities Institute.
LOCATION:Kresge Hall\, 1880 Campus Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/640750
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
